[B][SIZE=6]CustomDeathMessages 2.0.2[/SIZE][/B]

[B][SIZE=5]Highlights[/SIZE][/B]
[LIST]
[*]Minecraft 1.21+ support.
[*]Added Discord support for both [ICODE]EssentialsDiscord[/ICODE] and [ICODE]DiscordSRV[/ICODE].
[*]Added support for newer Minecraft damage and mob types, including [ICODE]Breeze[/ICODE] and [ICODE]Bogged[/ICODE].
[*]Improved compatibility with modern Paper versions.
[*]Improved delayed death handling so custom death messages are less likely to lose killer/cause data when other plugins delay death processing.
[/LIST]

[B][SIZE=5]Commands and Configuration[/SIZE][/B]
[LIST]
[*]Added [ICODE]/deathmessages[/ICODE] as a command alias.
[*]Improved [ICODE]/cdm reload[/ICODE] feedback when reload fails.
[*]Fixed the head drop chance config so [ICODE]drop-head-percentage[/ICODE] works as documented.
[*]Updated and expanded the default config and death-message lists.
[/LIST]

[B][SIZE=5]Defaults and Documentation[/SIZE][/B]
[LIST]
[*]Refreshed many bundled death messages with cleaner wording and broader coverage.
[*]Added default messages for [ICODE]Breeze[/ICODE].
[*]Changed [ICODE]enable-custom-name-entity-messages[/ICODE] to default to [ICODE]false[/ICODE].
[*]Updated the README to better match the plugin's current features, commands, placeholders, and integrations.
[*]Added a demo screenshot to the project documentation.
[/LIST]
